==English==

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪs|-eɪs]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb|effac|ing}}

# {{transitive}} To [[erase]] (as anything impressed or inscribed upon a surface); to render [[illegible]] or [[indiscernible]].
#:''The letters on the monument had been '''effaced''' by time and the touch of many hands.''
# {{transitive}} To cause to [[disappear]] as if by [[rub out|rubbbing out]] or [[strike out|striking out]].
#:''Three quarters of a bottle of vodka had done an effective job of '''effacing''' his memories of the previous night.''
# {{reflexive}} To make oneself [[inobtrusive]] as if due to [[modesty]] or [[diffidence]].
#:''Always the shy violet, Edna '''effaced''' herself in front of her sister, of whom she was in awe.''

